            <pb n="6" facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#k">The Volcano of Cotopaxi.</hi>&#x2014;</head>
                <p>The form of<lb break="yes"/>Cotopaxi is the most beautiful and regular of the<lb break="yes"/>colossal summits of the Andes. It is a perfect cone,<lb break="yes"/>which, covered with an enormous layer of snow,<lb break="yes" />shines with dazzling splendour at the setting of the<lb break="yes"/>sun, and detaches itself in the most picturesque manner<lb break="yes"/>from the azure vault of the sky. In scaling the volcano<lb break="yes"/>of Cotopaxi, it is extremely difficult to attain the<lb break="yes"/>inferior boundary of perpetual snow. On the south-<lb break="no"/>east of the mountain is a mass of rock, half-concealed<lb break="yes"/>under the snow, studded with points, and which the<lb break="yes"/>natives call &#x201C;the head of the Inca.&#x201D;&#x2014;<hi rendition="#i">Humboldt&#x2019;s<lb break="yes"/>Researches.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
